### Third-Party Files

This project includes code from the following third-party libraries, which are also licensed under the MIT License:

- [Microdot](https://github.com/miguelgrinberg/microdot) – MIT License  
  Microdot is a minimalist web framework for Python 3 that is compatible with microcontrollers.

- [SH1106](https://github.com/robert-hh/SH1106) – MIT License  
  SH1106 is a Python driver for the SH1106-based OLED displays.

- [Vue.js](https://vuejs.org/) – MIT License  
  Vue.js is a progressive JavaScript framework for building user interfaces.

- [Django](https://www.djangoproject.com/) – BSD License  
  Django is a high-level Python web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design.

For more details about the licenses of these third-party files, please refer to their respective LICENSE files or the documentation linked above.

